observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed to implement the following:

The management will prepare the Accomplishment Report carefully and properly;

The management will adhere to the GAD Budget in attributing expenditures under the GAD fund;

The management will consider amendment or revision of GAD Plan and Budget when there are new developments or situations, such as the Covid-19 situation, in order to give timely and necessary response to additional gender issues;

The management will refer to the provisions of DILG and CHR Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2020-01 dated July 15, 2020 in programing and implementing interventions in response to Covid-19;

the GAD Focal Person will put more effort in the implementation of the PPAs identified in its GAD Plan and Budget in accordance to Sec. 36 of Republic Act No. 9710; and

Make sure that at least 5 percent of the Municipality’s Budget is utilized for GAD related PPAs.

We recommended and the management agreed that the:
Inventory Committee conduct a complete physical count of property and equipment and prepare and submit the duly accomplished RPCPPE (Annex 49, Manual on the NGAS for LGUs, Volume 2) to the Audit Team;
Municipal General Services Officer prepare the PCs for each PPE account and update the records regularly;
Municipal General Services Officer reconcile their both records and do it regularly or every quarter, if possible; and
One-time cleansing of PPE account balances without available record of accountability should be availed of pursuant to the guidelines and procedures set forth in COA Circular No. 2020-006 to come up with reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to its existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended and the management agreed to:
Cancel the RIS issued for the equipments purchased and issue a corresponding ARE;
Submit to this office a copy of the properly issued ARE;
Review the previously issued RIS, cancel those that are issued for equipment and other properties and issue their corresponding ARE; and
Issue ARE correctly for future purchase and issuance of property and equipment and issue RIS for the issuance of supplies.

We recommended and the management agreed to implement the following:
The management will prepare the Accomplishment Report carefully and properly;
The management will adhere to the GAD Budget in attributing expenditures under the GAD fund;
The management will consider amendment or revision of GAD Plan and Budget when there are new developments or situations, such as the Covid-19 situation, in order to give timely and necessary response to additional gender issues;
The management will refer to the provisions of DILG and CHR Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2020-01 dated July 15, 2020 in programing and implementing interventions in response to Covid-19;
the GAD Focal Person will put more effort in the implementation of the PPAs identified in its GAD Plan and Budget in accordance to Sec. 36 of Republic Act No. 9710; and
Make sure that at least 5 percent of the Municipality’s Budget is utilized for GAD related PPAs.
